\frac{dV}{dt}=\frac{d}{dt}\left[\frac43\pi r^3\right]=\frac43\pi\frac{d}{dt}\left[r^3\right]=\frac43\pi\cdot 3r^2\frac{dr}{dt}=4\pi r^2\frac{dr}{dt}.
\displaystyle V=\frac43\pi r^3\implies \frac{dV}{dt}=\frac43\pi\cdot \frac{d(r^3)}{dr}\cdot\frac{dr}{dt}=4\pi r^2\frac{dr}{dt}
